name: fips
meaning: FIPS county code
formula_latex: @text{2 digits state FIPS code} + @text{(up to) 3 digits for county code}
remark: FIPS is federal Information Processing Standard

name: name_16
meaning: county name

name: statecode_prev
meaning: FIPS previous state code
remark: used for matching data between the NYT datasets

name: rep16_win
meaning: indicate whether Republican party win the county in 2016 election or not

name: rep12_win
meaning: indicate whether Republican party win the county in 2012 election or not

name: rep08_win
meaning: indicate whether Republican party win the county in 2008 election or not

name: votes16_trumpd
meaning: number of votes of Donald J. Trump

name: rep12
meaning: number of votes for republican party 2012

name: rep08
meaning: number of votes for republican party 2008

name: votes16_clintonh
meaning: number of votes of Hillary Clinton

name: dem12
meaning: number of votes for democratic party 2012

name: dem08
meaning: number of votes for democratic party 2008

name: votes16_others
meaning: number of votes of other parties than Democratic and Republic 2016

name: other12
meaning: number of votes for other party 2012

name: other08
meaning: number of votes for other party 2008

name: total16
meaning: total number of votes 2016

name: total12
meaning: total number of votes 2012

name: total08
meaning: total number of votes 2008

name: rep16_frac
meaning: vote fraction of republican 2016

name: rep12_frac
meaning: vote fraction of republican 2012

name: rep08_frac
meaning: vote fraction of republican 2008

name: dem16_frac
meaning: vote fraction of democratic 2016

name: dem12_frac
meaning: vote fraction of democratic 2012

name: dem08_frac
meaning: vote fraction of democratic 2008

name: other16_frac
meaning: vote fraction of other parties than Democratic and Republic 2016

name: other12_frac
meaning: vote fraction of other 2012

name: other08_frac
meaning: vote fraction of other 2008

name: est_votes_remaining
meaning: number of votes from unreported precincts in the county
remark: can be used to check which county has unreliable result

name: voting_age_population
meaning: number of people who are eligible to vote
remark: can be used to compute voting participation rate

name: voting_participation
meaning: percentage of population participated in the voting
formula_latex: @frac{@text{total number of votes in 2012}}{@text{total voting-population 2015}}@times{100}
remark: cannot use 2016 results to calculate this because we are trying to predict the result

name: voting_power
meaning: the power of each vote that counts towards the final vote of each state
formula_latex: @frac{@text{state electoral votes } @times @text{ total number of votes of the county}}{@text{total number of votes of the state}}

name: Total.Population
meaning: total population

name: population_density
meaning: population density
formula_latex: @frac{@text{total population}}{@text{total land area}}

name: sex_ratio
meaning: number of males per 100 females
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of males in the population}}{@text{number of females in the population}}@times{100}

name: age_dependency_ratio
meaning: number of dependents, aged zero to 14 and over the age of 65, to the total population, aged 15 to 64
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people not in working age}}{@text{number of people in working age}}@times{100}

name: median_age
meaning: median age

name: White.not.Latino.Population
meaning: percentage of  populaton identified themselves as white not latino
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people who idenfitied themselves as white (non-latino)}}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: African.American.Population
meaning: percentage of  populaton identified themselves as african american
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people who idenfitied themselves as african american }}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: Native.American.Population
meaning: percentage of  populaton identified themselves as native american
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people who idenfitied themselves as native american }}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: Asian.American.Population
meaning: percentage of  populaton identified themselves as asian american
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people who idenfitied themselves as asian american }}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: Population.some.other.race.or.races
meaning: percentage of  populaton identified themselves as other race
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people who idenfitied themselves as other races}}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: Latino.Population
meaning: percentage of  populaton identified themselves as latino/hispanic
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people who idenfitied themselves as latino/hispanic }}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: SIRE_homogeneity
meaning: Simpson index (or 1 - Simpson diversity index)

name: Gini.Coefficient
meaning: income inequality index
formula_latex: @text{formula depends on distribution of income}

name: Median.Earnings.2010.dollars
meaning: median earning of individuals

name: Children.Under.6.Living.in.Poverty
meaning: percentage of children under 6 living in poverty
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of children under 6 living in povery}}{@text{number of children under 6}}@times{100}

name: Child.Poverty.living.in.families.below.the.poverty.line
meaning: percentage of children living in families below poverty line
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of children living in families below poverty line}}{@text{number of children}}@times{100}

name: Adults.65.and.Older.Living.in.Poverty
display_name: Adults 65 and Older Living in Poverty
meaning: percentage of adults 65 and older living in poverty
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of adults 65 and older living in povery}}{@text{number of adults 65 and older}}@times{100}

name: Poverty.Rate.below.federal.poverty.threshold
meaning: poverty rate below federal poverty threshold
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people with income below federal poverty threshold}}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: Unemployment
meaning: percentage of population age >= 16 unemployed and/or looking for job
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people age} @geq 16 @text{ unemployed and/or looking for job}}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: Management.professional.and.related.occupations
meaning: percentage of population having management, professional, and related occupations
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people having management, professional, and related occupations}}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: Service.occupations
meaning: percentage of population having service occupations
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people having service occupations}}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: Sales.and.office.occupations
meaning: percentage of population having sales and office occupations
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people having sales and office occupations}}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: Farming.fishing.and.forestry.occupations
meaning: percentage of population having agricultural occupations
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people having agricultural occupations}}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: Construction.extraction.maintenance.and.repair.occupations
display_name: Construction, Extraction, Maintenance, and Repair Occupations
meaning: percentage of population having construction, extraction, maintenance, and repair occupations
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people having construction, extraction, maintenance, and repair occupations}}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: Production.transportation.and.material.moving.occupations
display_name: Production, Transportation, and Material moving Occupations
meaning: percentage of population having production, transportation, and material moving occupations
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people having production, transportation, and material moving occupations}}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: School.Enrollment
meaning: percentage of school enrollment
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of  actual students enrolled}}{@text{number of potential students enrolled}}@times{100}

name: Preschool.Enrollment.Ratio.enrolled.ages.3.and.4
meaning: percentage of preschool enrollment (between 3 and 4 years old)
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of actual children (between 3 and 4 years old) enrolled in preschool}}{@text{number of potential children enrolled in preschool}}@times{100}

name: Less.Than.High.School
meaning: percentage of population with education level less than highschool
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people with education level less than highschool}}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: At.Least.Bachelor.s.Degree
meaning: percentage of population with at least bachelor degree
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people with at least bachelor degree}}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: Graduate.Degree
meaning: percentage of population with graduate degree
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people with at least graduate degree}}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: life_expectancy
meaning: the average number of years a person born in a given country is expected to live if mortality rates at each age were to remain steady in the future

name: Infant.mortality
meaning: number of deaths of infants under 1 year old per 1,000 live births
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of deaths of infants under 1 year old}}{@text{number of live birth}}@times{1000}

name: Injury.deaths
meaning: injury mortality rate per 100,000
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of injury deaths}}{@text{total population}}@times{100000}

name: Poor.physical.health.days
display_name: Avg. No. of Physically Unhealthy Day
meaning: average number of reported physically unhealthy days per month

name: Poor.mental.health.days
display_name: Avg. No. of Mentally Unhealthy Day
meaning: average number of reported mentally unhealthy days per month

name: Low.birthweight
meaning: percentage of births with low birth weight (<2,500g)
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of births with low birth weight(< 2,500 g)}}{@text{number of births}}@times{100}

name: Teen.births
meaning: number of females ages 15-19 pregnant per 1,000
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of female age 15-19 pregnant}}{@text{number of female age 15-19}}@times{1000}

name: Children.in.single.parent.households
display_name: Children in Single Parent Households Rate
meaning: percentage of children living in single-parent household
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of children living in single-parent household}}{@text{number of children}}@times{100}

name: Adult.smoking
meaning: percentage of adults that reported currently smoking
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of adults reported currently smoking}}{@text{number of adults}}@times{100}

name: Adult.obesity
meaning: percentage of adults that report BMI >= 30
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of adults reported BMI} @geq 30}{@text{number of adults}}@times{100}

name: Diabetes
meaning: percentage of adults that reported currently having diabetes
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of adults currently reported having diabetes}}{@text{number of adults}}@times{100}

name: Sexually.transmitted.infections
meaning: number of Chlamydia case in population per 100,000
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people with Chlamydia}}{@text{total population}}@times{100000}

name: HIV.prevalence.rate
meaning: number of people living with HIV infection in a given population at a given period of time per 100,000
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people currently reported living with HIV infection}}{@text{total population}}@times{100000}

name: Uninsured
meaning: percentage of population under 65 without insurance
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of people under 65 without insurance}}{@text{total population}}@times{100}

name: Violent.crime
meaning: number of crimes reported to law enforcement agencies per 100,000 total population
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of violent crimes}}{@text{total population}}@times{100000}

name: Homicide.rate
meaning: homicide mortality rate per 100,000 total population
formula_latex: @frac{@text{number of homicide crimes}}{@text{total population}}@times{100000}

name: winter_PRCP
meaning: winter precipitation

name: winter_TAVG
meaning: winter average temperature
